{
  "stem": "8892.2",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The furniture was out of the room, and they shoved us two families-- two or three of us-- Weiss family, which had seven of us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We are six, two sisters, two young brothers, and my father-- about 14, 15 people to one room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And whatever we had with us, we just laid it on the floor, and that's where we are.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the ghetto was also terrible, crazy chaos, because they didn't know what the heck they're going to do with us or what's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] What happen is, you were allowed to take as much as you can carry food-- that I remember.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my mother would make in a jar-- that I remember distinctly-- a base, a soup base, just like we buy it in cubes now, they made at home with the schmaltz and flour and seasoning.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they put it in a big jar, because in Europe in a small town you stored everything.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was still kind of spring and winter, so you had plenty of fat and plenty of flour, because we never went hungry, no matter how the [INAUDIBLE] was, my father always, always managed to put food on a table.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had the bread and the challah and all this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there, when they knew that we're going, I remember my mother and my sister, she was so weak.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then she organized to make a lot of this paste, put it in a big jar, and we carried that with us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we get into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's no ration of food, nothing, just what you were carrying.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, two, three days later, they notice there is no food for all these people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this just wasn't Olaszliszka.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
